  [Text] <LOCATION>Bucharest ROMPRES</LOCATION>, 18/4/1994 -- In the presence of 
<PERSON>Jean Paul-Carteron</PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION>Forum Foundation</ORGANIZATION>, of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Romanian Government</ORGANIZATION>'s secretary-general and secretary-general of 
the <ORGANIZATION>Crans Montana Conference</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> Viorel Hrebenciuc and 
numerous mass media representatives the press centre was 
inaugurated on 18 <DATE>April</DATE> of the <ORGANIZATION>Crans Montana Forum</ORGANIZATION> due in 
<LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> over <DATE>21-24 April</DATE>. <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman Simona 
Miculescu</ORGANIZATION> will be spokeswoman also of the centre. 
  The press centre will issue every morning a document in 
Romanian, English and French with details of the day's schedule. 
It will also issue daily press releases in Romanian, French and 
English referring to the debates in plenum and in the sections 
on themes. They will comprise syntheses of the participants' 
addresses. Journalists will also receive Romanian and foreign 
press reviews, home and foreign news supplied by the ROMPRES 
national news agency, the texts of the statements and addresses 
of the previous day's speakers, other publications. The 
spokesperson will meet the journalists daily at 1300 hours [1000 
GMT]. Journalists that want to contact various personalities 
will apply directly to the office set up to this end under the 
conference's secretariat general. The press office will 
function daily between 0800 hours [0500 GMT] and <DATE>2000</DATE> [1700 
GMT]. It will accommodate also offices of the national radio, 
television and of ROMPRES. The documents issued by the press 
centre will not be official. 
  So far, the following heads of state have confirmed their 
participation in the <LOCATION>Crans-Montana</LOCATION> Forum: of <LOCATION>Cyprus</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Belarus</LOCATION>, 
<LOCATION>Estonia</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Yugoslavia</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Lithuania</LOCATION> and the <ORGANIZATION>Palestine Liberation 
Organization</ORGANIZATION>. All in all there will be 1,100 participants and 
700 journalists. Mme. <PERSON>Catherine Lalumiere</PERSON> will be present on 
the presidium at the inaugural session. Participating will also 
be nine prime ministers and deputy prime ministers, five 
parliament presidents and speakers, 12 foreign ministers and 
deputy foreign ministers, 20 ministers, 17 ambassadors, 12 
secretaries-general and assistant secretaries-general of 
international organizations, 67 members of the diplomatic corps 
accredited in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION>, 129 other political personalities. 
  The meeting of the <ORGANIZATION>Crans Montana Forum</ORGANIZATION>, a world-scale event, 
is going to take place over <DATE>April 21-24</DATE> in <LOCATION>Bucharest</LOCATION> at the 
<ORGANIZATION>Parliament Palace</ORGANIZATION>, one of the world's largest buildings. 
  With a surface of 508,000 square meters, <LOCATION>Romania</LOCATION>'s 
<ORGANIZATION>Parliament 
Palace</ORGANIZATION> is mentioned by the Guiness book of records as the second 
largest administrative building in the world, next to the 
<ORGANIZATION>Pentagon</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Washington</LOCATION> with a total surface of 604,000 square 
meters. 
  In point of the constructed volume, the palace is world's 
third with 2,550,000 square meters, next to a sky-rockets 
assembling building in <LOCATION>Cape Canevral</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION>, with 3,666,000 
square meters and Quetzalcoatl Pyramid at <LOCATION>Cholula</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>, with 
3,300,000 square meters, but ahead of the Keops pyramid ranked 
fourth with 2,500,000 square meters. 
  The construction works started on <DATE>June 25, 1984</DATE>, and 
swallowed about 480,000 cubic meters of high-quality cement, 
65,000 tonnes of steel for reinforced concrete, 42,000 tonnes of 
rolled steel. 
  The palace is furnished with a 286,000 square meter green 
backyard. 
  The building is the outcome of a great national effort, 
starting from its design and erection and ending with the 
materials suppliers, everything is Romanian. About 17,000 
people have worked on the building site. 
  Along with numerous main and secondary offices, reception 
rooms, meeting rooms, a plenary sitting room of the <ORGANIZATION>Chamber of 
Deputies</ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION>Parliament</ORGANIZATION>'s Palace has also a set of halls, rooms 
and lobbies impressing through astonishing elegance, size, 
furnishings and design, bearing names such as the main hall, the 
honorary gallery, the hall of the provinces, the union hall, the 
lobby of the union hall, the human rights hall. 

</TEXT>

